# events

**Instance Property**

A chronologically ordered array of player item access log events.

## Declaration

```swift
var events: [AVPlayerItemAccessLogEvent] { get }
```

## Discussion

The array contains [doc://com.apple.avfoundation/documentation/AVFoundation/AVPlayerItemAccessLogEvent] objects that represent the chronological sequence of events contained in the access log.

This property isn’t observable. For more information about key-value observing, see [doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/Swift/using-key-value-observing-in-swift].

## Accessing log data

- **extendedLogData()**: Returns a serialized representation of the access log in the Extended Log File Format.
- **extendedLogDataStringEncoding**: The string encoding of the extended log data.
